package main

// planetInSignText holds specific interpretations for every planet-in-sign combo.
// Key format: "Planet_Sign"
var planetInSignText = map[string]string{

	// ── SUN ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"Sun_Aries": "With your Sun in Aries, you are a trailblazer at heart — your identity is built on initiative, courage, and the thrill of being first. You need to lead, to act, and to forge your own path without being slowed down by others. Your vitality is highest when you are taking on new challenges and proving your independence.",
	"Sun_Taurus": "With your Sun in Taurus, your identity is rooted in stability, sensuality, and the slow cultivation of beauty and comfort. You build your sense of self through what you create and accumulate — not through speed, but through patient, enduring effort. Your vitality is tied to the physical world: good food, beautiful surroundings, and financial security all nourish your core.",
	"Sun_Gemini": "With your Sun in Gemini, your identity is defined by your mind — you are a natural communicator, learner, and connector of ideas. You feel most yourself when you are engaged in conversation, gathering information, or switching between multiple interests with fluid ease. Your vitality depends on mental stimulation; boredom is your nemesis.",
	"Sun_Cancer": "With your Sun in Cancer, your identity is inseparable from your emotional world — your history, your family, and your need to nurture and protect those you love. You are at your most vital when you feel emotionally secure and are building a home or legacy that truly belongs to you. Sensitivity is not weakness for you — it is the source of your deepest strength.",
	"Sun_Leo": "With your Sun in Leo, you are built to shine — your identity is centered on creative self-expression, generosity of spirit, and the desire to be recognized for your unique gifts. You come alive in the spotlight and thrive when you are given the freedom to perform, create, or lead. Your sense of self is strongest when you are being truly, fully yourself — not hiding, not dimming your light for anyone.",
	"Sun_Virgo": "With your Sun in Virgo, your identity is shaped by your drive to improve, analyze, and be of practical service. You feel most yourself when you are mastering a craft, solving a problem, or contributing something genuinely useful to the world. Your vitality is rooted in purposeful, precise work — you need to feel that what you do matters and that you are doing it well.",
	"Sun_Libra": "With your Sun in Libra, your identity is shaped by relationship — you define yourself through the mirror of others and through your commitment to fairness, beauty, and harmony. You are at your best when you are collaborating, creating aesthetic experiences, or mediating between opposing forces. Learning to have a clear, independent sense of self within partnership is one of your core life themes.",
	"Sun_Scorpio": "With your Sun in Scorpio, your identity runs deep — you are driven by a need to understand what lies beneath the surface, to transform through intensity, and to live with total psychological honesty. You feel most yourself in situations that demand courage, depth, and the willingness to face difficult truths. Your power lies in your capacity to regenerate — to turn loss and crisis into profound personal strength.",
	"Sun_Sagittarius": "With your Sun in Sagittarius, your identity is shaped by your need for freedom, expansion, and the pursuit of meaning. You feel most yourself when you are exploring — whether through travel, philosophy, learning, or adventure — and when your life points toward a horizon worth chasing. Optimism and conviction are central to who you are; you are at your best when you have a vision that fires your enthusiasm.",
	"Sun_Capricorn": "With your Sun in Capricorn, your identity is built on ambition, discipline, and the long patient work of building something that will last. You feel most yourself when you are working toward a worthy goal, earning authority through demonstrated competence, and proving your reliability over time. Your vitality is tied to achievement — not for show, but for the deep satisfaction of having truly earned your place.",
	"Sun_Aquarius": "With your Sun in Aquarius, your identity is inseparable from your individuality and your commitment to a larger vision. You feel most yourself when you are thinking independently, challenging convention, or contributing to something that moves humanity forward. You need freedom — both from conformity and from the expectations of the crowd — to express the full breadth of who you are.",
	"Sun_Pisces": "With your Sun in Pisces, your identity is fluid, compassionate, and attuned to the invisible currents of life. You feel most yourself in creative, spiritual, or empathic contexts where imagination and intuition can flow freely. Your sense of self is tied to your inner life more than your outer achievements — and your greatest strength is your capacity to feel, dream, and transcend ordinary reality.",

	// ── MOON ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"Moon_Aries": "With your Moon in Aries, you feel emotions quickly, intensely, and directly — and just as quickly, you move on. Your emotional security comes from autonomy: you need to feel free to act on your impulses without being held back. In times of stress your instinct is to confront and assert rather than to withdraw.",
	"Moon_Taurus": "With your Moon in Taurus, you are emotionally grounded, steady, and deeply comforted by physical stability — familiar routines, beautiful surroundings, and reliable security. You resist emotional upheaval with everything you have, and once you feel settled your warmth and loyalty are among your most enduring qualities.",
	"Moon_Gemini": "With your Moon in Gemini, your emotional world is expressed through words and ideas rather than raw feeling — you process emotion by talking about it, analyzing it, or distracting yourself with mental activity. You need variety and intellectual stimulation to feel at ease; your moods shift quickly and can be hard to pin down even for you.",
	"Moon_Cancer": "With your Moon in Cancer, the Moon is in its home sign — you are profoundly intuitive, empathic, and deeply tied to your emotional roots. Your security comes from home, family, and belonging, and you are among the most nurturing of all lunar placements. Your memory is long and your feelings run deep; you carry the past with you wherever you go.",
	"Moon_Leo": "With your Moon in Leo, you need warmth, recognition, and creative expression to feel emotionally secure. Your emotions are big, generous, and theatrical — you love with your whole heart and expect the same in return. Feeling overlooked cuts deeply; at your best, your emotional warmth lights up every room you enter.",
	"Moon_Virgo": "With your Moon in Virgo, you process emotions analytically — you feel better once you understand what you are feeling and why. Security comes from order, usefulness, and a practical sense of control over your environment. You may struggle to simply receive care without offering something in return; that willingness to be tended to is a lifelong practice.",
	"Moon_Libra": "With your Moon in Libra, you need harmony, beauty, and partnership to feel emotionally balanced. Conflict and ugliness are genuinely disturbing to you, and you instinctively work to restore equilibrium. Your emotional security is tied to your relationships — when your close bonds are healthy, you thrive; when they are strained, your inner world feels off-kilter.",
	"Moon_Scorpio": "With your Moon in Scorpio, your emotional life is intense, private, and extraordinarily deep. You feel everything powerfully but reveal almost nothing on the surface — you are the person in the room who notices everything while showing little. Your security comes from depth of connection and absolute trust; betrayal hits harder for you than almost anyone else.",
	"Moon_Sagittarius": "With your Moon in Sagittarius, your emotional security comes from freedom, exploration, and a sense of expanding horizons. You tend to be optimistic and philosophically resilient — when something goes wrong, you look for the broader meaning. Emotional confinement or pessimism are genuinely unsettling to you; you need room to roam.",
	"Moon_Capricorn": "With your Moon in Capricorn, your emotional nature is controlled, reserved, and quietly ambitious. You feel secure when you have clear structure and a sense of upward progress. Vulnerability can be difficult — you tend to manage emotion through work and achievement rather than open expression. Over time you learn that allowing yourself to feel is not weakness but strength.",
	"Moon_Aquarius": "With your Moon in Aquarius, your emotional style is cool, detached, and intellectually oriented. You experience feelings from a slight remove rather than being swept away by them. Security comes from independence, friendship, and a sense that you are living according to your own authentic values rather than the expectations of others.",
	"Moon_Pisces": "With your Moon in Pisces, your emotional world is oceanic — boundless, empathic, and in constant flux. You absorb the feelings of those around you without trying, and your compassion is one of your deepest gifts. Maintaining your own emotional boundaries so that you do not lose yourself in others' feelings is essential; solitude and spiritual practice restore you.",

	// ── MERCURY ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"Mercury_Aries": "With Mercury in Aries, your mind is fast, direct, and decisive — you think in terms of action and conclusions, not endless deliberation. You communicate with confidence and sometimes impatience, preferring frank exchanges over diplomatic hedging. You are at your intellectual best when under pressure or breaking new mental ground.",
	"Mercury_Taurus": "With Mercury in Taurus, your thinking is methodical, grounded, and deliberate — you take time to form your opinions, but once formed they are nearly impossible to shift. You have a strong practical intelligence and communicate with patience and sensory precision. You absorb information best through repetition, hands-on experience, and real-world application.",
	"Mercury_Gemini": "With Mercury in Gemini, the planet is in one of its home signs — your mind is quick, curious, and effortlessly multi-tasking. You can hold multiple perspectives simultaneously and thrive where verbal agility and intellectual range are rewarded. Your communication is witty and highly adaptable; the challenge is following through on ideas long enough to bring them to fruition.",
	"Mercury_Cancer": "With Mercury in Cancer, your thinking is shaped by memory, emotion, and intuition rather than cold logic. You absorb information through feeling and are particularly attuned to the emotional subtext of conversations — what is being said beneath the words. You communicate with warmth and personal depth, and you have a remarkable ability to recall the emotional texture of past experiences.",
	"Mercury_Leo": "With Mercury in Leo, your mind is dramatic, creative, and confident — you think in stories and have a natural gift for capturing attention with your words. You communicate with flair and authority and tend to present your ideas with conviction and pride. You think best when you are inspired and performing; you need an audience to bring out your best mental work.",
	"Mercury_Virgo": "With Mercury in Virgo, the planet is in its other home sign — your mind is precise, analytical, and exceptionally detail-oriented. You are a natural critic and editor: you see what others miss, refine what others leave rough, and communicate with careful accuracy. Your intellectual gift is in making complex things comprehensible through rigorous, methodical analysis.",
	"Mercury_Libra": "With Mercury in Libra, your thinking is balanced, diplomatic, and aesthetically oriented — you instinctively consider multiple sides before forming a judgment and communicate with grace and tact. You have a natural gift for mediation and a keen eye for what is fair and beautiful. The challenge is decision paralysis: seeing all sides equally can make it difficult to commit.",
	"Mercury_Scorpio": "With Mercury in Scorpio, your mind penetrates beneath the surface — you think in depth, intensity, and psychological complexity. You are drawn to secrets, mysteries, and the hidden motivations that others overlook, and your communication can be powerfully probing or deliberately strategic. Your words carry weight; you rarely say anything casually.",
	"Mercury_Sagittarius": "With Mercury in Sagittarius, your thinking is expansive, philosophical, and optimistic — you are most interested in the big picture, the broad principles, and the overarching meaning. You communicate with enthusiasm and conviction and have a gift for inspiring others with ideas. Detail work and follow-through are less appealing; your strength is in vision and synthesis.",
	"Mercury_Capricorn": "With Mercury in Capricorn, your thinking is disciplined, structured, and goal-oriented — you communicate with authority and prefer information that is practical, concrete, and useful. You take ideas seriously and develop them with long-term application in mind. Your intellectual style is thorough and patient; you prefer to say less but say it well.",
	"Mercury_Aquarius": "With Mercury in Aquarius, your thinking is original, independent, and ahead of its time — you approach problems from unusual angles and are unafraid to challenge consensus. You communicate in a way that is clear, detached, and often intellectually provocative. Your mind is genuinely innovative; you think best when given the freedom to overturn assumptions.",
	"Mercury_Pisces": "With Mercury in Pisces, your thinking is intuitive, imaginative, and non-linear — you process information through images, feelings, and impressions rather than strict logic. You have a gift for poetry, metaphor, and creative synthesis. Communication is most natural for you when it blurs the boundary between rational thought and artistic expression.",

	// ── VENUS ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"Venus_Aries": "With Venus in Aries, in love you are bold, direct, and passionate — you fall fast and pursue what you want with undisguised enthusiasm. You are attracted to confidence, energy, and a degree of challenge; the thrill of pursuit is part of what excites you. Your values are centered on independence and authenticity, and you need a partner who can keep up with your pace.",
	"Venus_Taurus": "With Venus in Taurus, the planet is in her home sign — your approach to love is sensual, steady, and deeply loyal. You value security, physical comfort, and the slow building of something lasting; you are not interested in emotional rollercoasters. Beauty, pleasure, and material ease are important to you, and you express love through practical devotion and physical presence.",
	"Venus_Gemini": "With Venus in Gemini, in love you are playful, curious, and in need of constant intellectual stimulation. You are attracted to wit, versatility, and people who can surprise you with their minds. Boredom is the death knell of your relationships; you stay in love with partners who keep you guessing and growing.",
	"Venus_Cancer": "With Venus in Cancer, in love you are nurturing, deeply loyal, and emotionally sensitive. You value emotional security above all else and tend to love with protective intensity. You create home and belonging for those you love, and you need a partner who makes you feel genuinely safe and cherished in return.",
	"Venus_Leo": "With Venus in Leo, in love you are warm, dramatic, and generous — you give extravagantly and expect the same devotion in return. You are attracted to confidence, vitality, and people who make you feel special. Romance is important to you; you want love to be an adventure, a performance, a grand and beautiful thing.",
	"Venus_Virgo": "With Venus in Virgo, your approach to love is practical, attentive, and expressed through service rather than grand gesture. You show affection through small, thoughtful acts — noticing what someone needs and quietly providing it. You are attracted to intelligence and competence; your standards are high, but so is your devotion once you commit.",
	"Venus_Libra": "With Venus in Libra, the planet is in her other home sign — your approach to love is gracious, romantic, and deeply oriented toward harmony. You are a skilled partner: fair, affectionate, and genuinely invested in the quality of your relationships. You are drawn to beauty, refinement, and people who are willing to meet you halfway.",
	"Venus_Scorpio": "With Venus in Scorpio, in love you are intensely private, deeply loyal, and driven by a need for complete psychological intimacy. You want to know the person you love at the deepest level — no surface connection will satisfy you. Your love is all-or-nothing; betrayal hits harder than almost any other wound, but your devotion, once given, is absolute.",
	"Venus_Sagittarius": "With Venus in Sagittarius, in love you are adventurous, free-spirited, and in need of a partner who shares your love of growth and exploration. You are attracted to people with a strong philosophy, a sense of humor, and an appetite for life. Freedom is non-negotiable; a relationship that feels confining will not hold your attention for long.",
	"Venus_Capricorn": "With Venus in Capricorn, your approach to love is serious, patient, and oriented toward long-term stability. You need to respect someone before you can love them, and you show affection through reliability and steadfast presence. You tend to take commitment seriously and build love the way you build everything else — slowly and well.",
	"Venus_Aquarius": "With Venus in Aquarius, in love you value friendship, intellectual equality, and personal freedom above conventional romance. You are attracted to people who are unique, independent, and unafraid to be different. You need a relationship that has room for both partners to grow as individuals; too much possessiveness will drive you away.",
	"Venus_Pisces": "With Venus in Pisces, your love is compassionate, idealistic, and boundless. You are drawn to beauty, vulnerability, and spiritual connection, and you love with a selfless, almost transcendent quality. The challenge is maintaining healthy boundaries and distinguishing between genuine love and the beautiful dream of it.",

	// ── MARS ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"Mars_Aries": "With Mars in Aries, the planet is in its home sign — your drive is at its most raw, fast, and direct. You pursue what you want without hesitation and your energy is at its best in competitive, fast-moving situations. Your instinct is to act first and think later; the challenge is developing patience and follow-through alongside your formidable initiative.",
	"Mars_Taurus": "With Mars in Taurus, your drive is slow to ignite but extraordinarily persistent once it does. You pursue your goals with methodical, relentless determination — you are not the fastest starter, but you almost never quit. You are most effective when you can work at your own pace and build steadily toward tangible results.",
	"Mars_Gemini": "With Mars in Gemini, your drive is expressed through words, ideas, and the swift exchange of information. You pursue multiple goals simultaneously and are energized by variety and mental challenge. Your assertiveness is often verbal — you debate, persuade, and argue with skill. The challenge is channeling this scattered energy into sustained action toward a single goal.",
	"Mars_Cancer": "With Mars in Cancer, your drive is emotional and protective — you are most motivated when fighting for those you love or defending something deeply personal. Your energy ebbs and flows with your moods; you are capable of fierce action when your security is threatened, but you can also retreat under stress. Learning to assert yourself directly rather than indirectly is a key growth area.",
	"Mars_Leo": "With Mars in Leo, your drive is bold, creative, and fueled by pride. You pursue what you want with theatrical confidence and a need to be admired for how you go about it. You are at your most energized when you have an audience and a worthy stage, fighting hardest for things that allow you to express your unique identity and creative vision.",
	"Mars_Virgo": "With Mars in Virgo, your drive is precise, analytical, and directed toward improvement. You are most effective when working on clearly defined tasks where your skill and attention to detail produce measurably excellent results. You can be a hard and tireless worker, but perfectionism that slows your action or turns inward as self-criticism is the shadow to watch.",
	"Mars_Libra": "With Mars in Libra, your drive is channeled through partnership and diplomacy — you are most motivated in collaborative situations and can be a powerfully persuasive negotiator. The challenge is direct assertion: you may struggle with indecision or passive aggression. Finding your own clear desire beneath the desire for harmony is a core life theme.",
	"Mars_Scorpio": "With Mars in Scorpio, your drive is intense, strategic, and formidable — you pursue your goals with focused determination and the ability to sustain effort through situations that would break others. You rarely reveal your hand, and you are at your most powerful when operating from a position of psychological depth and strategic patience.",
	"Mars_Sagittarius": "With Mars in Sagittarius, your drive is enthusiastic, expansive, and fueled by a sense of adventure and purpose. You are most energized when pursuing goals that feel meaningful, and you bring enormous passion to causes and visions that excite you. The challenge is that your fire can scatter — bringing your legendary enthusiasm to one sustained commitment is the work.",
	"Mars_Capricorn": "With Mars in Capricorn, your drive is disciplined, strategic, and oriented toward long-term achievement. You do not waste energy; every action is calculated to bring you closer to a clearly defined goal. Patient, methodical, and capable of extraordinary ambition executed with calm efficiency — this is one of the most effective Mars placements.",
	"Mars_Aquarius": "With Mars in Aquarius, your drive is channeled through ideas, principles, and collective action. You are most energized when pursuing goals that serve a larger vision or challenge an unjust status quo. Your assertiveness is often intellectual and can be surprisingly rebellious; you have little patience for authority that cannot justify itself through reason.",
	"Mars_Pisces": "With Mars in Pisces, your drive is subtle, diffuse, and channeled through imagination, compassion, and spiritual motivation. You are most effective working behind the scenes or in service of a creative or idealistic goal. Direct confrontation can be uncomfortable; your strength lies in perseverance, adaptability, and the ability to act without the need for recognition.",

	// ── JUPITER ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"Jupiter_Aries": "With Jupiter in Aries, your growth and good fortune come through boldness, initiative, and willingness to be first. You expand your life by striking out independently and trusting your instincts without waiting for permission. Opportunities tend to arrive precisely when you take courageous, unplanned action.",
	"Jupiter_Taurus": "With Jupiter in Taurus, your growth comes through patience, sensory experience, and the steady accumulation of natural and material abundance. You expand by building lasting things, cultivating beauty, and honoring the physical world. Financial growth tends to reward your reliable, practical approach over time.",
	"Jupiter_Gemini": "With Jupiter in Gemini, your growth comes through learning, communication, and the rich exchange of ideas. You expand by exposing yourself to diverse people, subjects, and environments. Your greatest opportunities arise through intellectual curiosity and your gift for making connections between disparate worlds.",
	"Jupiter_Cancer": "With Jupiter in Cancer, your growth comes through emotional intelligence, nurturing, and a deep attunement to home and family. You expand by honoring your instincts, deepening your roots, and creating a sense of belonging for yourself and others. Abundance tends to find you when you lead with genuine compassion.",
	"Jupiter_Leo": "With Jupiter in Leo, your growth comes through creative self-expression, leadership, and the generous sharing of your gifts. You expand by being fully, authentically yourself on the largest stage you can find. Opportunities tend to arrive through your charisma, generosity, and willingness to perform and inspire.",
	"Jupiter_Virgo": "With Jupiter in Virgo, your growth comes through service, mastery of craft, and the disciplined refinement of your skills. You expand by being genuinely useful and paying attention to what others overlook. Your greatest fortune arrives through work done with integrity and precision rather than through dramatic gestures.",
	"Jupiter_Libra": "With Jupiter in Libra, your growth comes through partnership, diplomacy, and the cultivation of beauty and fairness. You expand through close alliances, creative collaborations, and the pursuit of harmony and aesthetic excellence. Opportunities tend to arrive through the relationships you invest in most wholeheartedly.",
	"Jupiter_Scorpio": "With Jupiter in Scorpio, your growth comes through depth, transformation, and the willingness to face what others avoid. You expand by investigating what lies beneath the surface, embracing change, and using crisis as fuel for regeneration. Your greatest opportunities often come disguised as endings or loss.",
	"Jupiter_Sagittarius": "With Jupiter in Sagittarius, the planet is in its home sign — growth is at its most natural and abundant. You expand through travel, philosophy, higher education, and the pursuit of meaning. Your optimism and conviction are contagious, and your greatest opportunities arrive when you are living fully according to your principles.",
	"Jupiter_Capricorn": "With Jupiter in Capricorn, your growth comes through discipline, long-term planning, and the patient building of authority. You expand by setting ambitious goals and pursuing them with methodical focus. Abundance rewards your reliability, ambition, and willingness to put in the necessary time without looking for shortcuts.",
	"Jupiter_Aquarius": "With Jupiter in Aquarius, your growth comes through innovation, community, and the pursuit of a collective vision. You expand by challenging convention, building networks, and contributing to something larger than yourself. Opportunities arrive when you are thinking ahead of the curve and trusting your most unconventional ideas.",
	"Jupiter_Pisces": "With Jupiter in Pisces, your growth comes through compassion, spirituality, and the surrender of ego to something larger. You expand through creative and spiritual practice, empathy for others, and a willingness to trust the invisible currents of life. Abundance tends to flow most freely when you release rigid control.",

	// ── SATURN ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"Saturn_Aries": "With Saturn in Aries, your life lesson involves learning to temper impulsiveness with discipline and to assert yourself without aggression or fear. You may have struggled with confidence in initiating action or with a sense that your desires are somehow not permitted. Over time you build a powerful, patient self-determination that is all the more effective for being hard-won.",
	"Saturn_Taurus": "With Saturn in Taurus, your life lesson involves confronting issues of material security, self-worth, and the patient accumulation of resources. You may have grown up with financial instability or a complicated relationship with your own value. Over time you build a stable, enduring relationship with the material world through persistent effort and sound judgment.",
	"Saturn_Gemini": "With Saturn in Gemini, your life lesson involves developing disciplined, precise communication and the capacity to focus your mind rather than scatter it. You may have struggled with early learning difficulties or a sense that your intelligence was not recognized. Over time you build a rigorous, authoritative mental discipline that more than compensates for early doubts.",
	"Saturn_Cancer": "With Saturn in Cancer, your life lesson involves confronting emotional security, the wounds of family, and the challenge of nurturing without losing yourself. You may have experienced emotional withholding or excessive responsibility in childhood. Over time you build a deep, self-sufficient emotional foundation from which you can nurture others with genuine inner strength.",
	"Saturn_Leo": "With Saturn in Leo, your life lesson involves confronting ego, creative expression, and the fear of being truly seen. You may have struggled with self-doubt or inhibition around your gifts, or with a childhood that discouraged self-expression. Over time you build a quiet, hard-earned confidence and a creative discipline that produces work of lasting significance.",
	"Saturn_Virgo": "With Saturn in Virgo, your life lesson involves mastering the fine line between healthy discernment and crippling self-criticism. You are capable of extraordinary precision and craftsmanship, but you must learn to direct your high standards productively rather than turning them against yourself. Mastery and genuine usefulness are the rewards of this placement.",
	"Saturn_Libra": "With Saturn in Libra, the planet is exalted — your life lesson involves developing mature, fair, and equitable relationships and a real understanding of justice. You take commitment seriously and hold high standards for partnership. Over time you become a model of fairness and diplomatic authority whose balanced judgments others genuinely trust.",
	"Saturn_Scorpio": "With Saturn in Scorpio, your life lesson involves confronting power, control, loss, and the depths of your own psychology. Saturn here pushes you to develop psychological integrity and to handle power — both your own and others' — with full accountability. Transformation through crisis is a recurring theme, and you build formidable inner strength through it.",
	"Saturn_Sagittarius": "With Saturn in Sagittarius, your life lesson involves developing a genuine, tested philosophical worldview rather than a borrowed or superficial one. You may have experienced the collapse of belief systems you once relied on. Over time you build a rigorous, personally earned philosophy that guides your life with real wisdom rather than inherited doctrine.",
	"Saturn_Capricorn": "With Saturn in Capricorn, the planet is in its home sign — the lessons of discipline, responsibility, and long-term achievement are powerfully emphasized. You have an innate understanding of how structures work and an uncommon capacity for sustained effort. The danger is workaholism or emotional constriction; the reward is real, enduring achievement built brick by brick.",
	"Saturn_Aquarius": "With Saturn in Aquarius, your life lesson involves balancing radical individuality with responsibility to the collective. You may have felt like an outsider or struggled to find your place within groups. Over time you develop a principled, disciplined vision for the future that earns you genuine authority within communities committed to progress and reform.",
	"Saturn_Pisces": "With Saturn in Pisces, your life lesson involves developing spiritual maturity, healthy boundaries, and the capacity to serve without self-dissolution. You may have struggled with boundary confusion, escapism, or the weight of others' suffering. Over time you develop a grounded, practical spirituality and a compassionate discipline that serves the world without depleting you.",

	// ── URANUS ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"Uranus_Aries": "With Uranus in Aries, your generation carries an impulse toward radical individual reinvention and the disruption of old power structures. Personally, this placement energizes your capacity for sudden, decisive reinvention of your identity. Change tends to arrive through bold, unplanned breaks from the past that free you to start entirely fresh.",
	"Uranus_Taurus": "With Uranus in Taurus, your generation is rewriting humanity's relationship with money, land, and material resources. Personally, this placement creates unexpected upheavals in your financial life and value system — the ground shifts under your feet when you least expect it. The invitation is to discover your security in something beyond material accumulation.",
	"Uranus_Gemini": "With Uranus in Gemini, your generation revolutionized communication and the way humans exchange ideas. Personally, this placement creates a restless, innovative mind that operates best outside conventional mental structures. Your thinking is ahead of its time, and you are drawn to the unexplored edges of language and information.",
	"Uranus_Cancer": "With Uranus in Cancer, your generation disrupted traditional family structures and redefined home and belonging. Personally, this placement creates unexpected upheavals around home, family, and emotional security. Your sense of belonging is built on your own original terms rather than the models you inherited.",
	"Uranus_Leo": "With Uranus in Leo, your generation revolutionized self-expression, creativity, and the concept of individual identity. Personally, this placement creates a need for radical authenticity, a disruptive creative energy, and a refusal to conform in how you present yourself to the world.",
	"Uranus_Virgo": "With Uranus in Virgo, your generation revolutionized work, health, and systems of service. Personally, this placement creates an innovative, nontraditional approach to work and wellness. You are drawn to unconventional methods and systemic improvements that challenge how things have always been done.",
	"Uranus_Libra": "With Uranus in Libra, your generation disrupted conventional partnership structures and redefined equality and justice. Personally, this placement creates an unconventional approach to relationship — you are drawn to non-traditional partnership models and a progressive, independent-minded understanding of fairness.",
	"Uranus_Scorpio": "With Uranus in Scorpio, your generation disrupted the hidden structures of power, sexuality, and shared resources. Personally, this placement generates sudden, radical transformation at the deepest psychological levels — the kind of change that rewrites who you are at the root.",
	"Uranus_Sagittarius": "With Uranus in Sagittarius, your generation disrupted established philosophical, religious, and educational systems. Personally, this placement creates a restless hunger for freedom and truth that refuses to be confined by any single belief system. Your most liberating moments come through questioning the beliefs you were handed.",
	"Uranus_Capricorn": "With Uranus in Capricorn, your generation is dismantling and rebuilding established power structures and institutions. Personally, this placement creates an innovative approach to career and social structures, with a drive to reform systems from the inside rather than simply rebelling from the outside.",
	"Uranus_Aquarius": "With Uranus in Aquarius, the planet is in its home sign — your generation carries a concentrated impulse toward collective awakening, technological revolution, and humanitarian reinvention. Personally, this placement makes you a natural innovator: fiercely independent, oriented toward the future, and ahead of your time.",
	"Uranus_Pisces": "With Uranus in Pisces, your generation is dissolving old boundaries between spiritual traditions and revolutionizing how art and imagination shape shared reality. Personally, this placement creates sudden spiritual awakenings, unusual intuitive sensitivity, and a tendency to have the old illusions you rely on dissolved when you need it most.",

	// ── NEPTUNE ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"Neptune_Aries": "With Neptune in Aries, spiritual idealism manifests as an individualistic, pioneering vision — the lone mystic rather than the institutional believer. Your imagination and sense of the divine are animated by independence and the courage to venture into the unknown alone.",
	"Neptune_Taurus": "With Neptune in Taurus, your spiritual and creative ideals are grounded in the material world — beauty, nature, and the senses carry a transcendent quality for you. Personally, this placement gently dissolves rigid material attachments, inviting you to find the sacred in sensory experience.",
	"Neptune_Gemini": "With Neptune in Gemini, your ideals flow through communication and language — words themselves carry a dreamlike, spiritually charged quality. Your imagination is endlessly versatile, and you may experience the world as a fluid interplay of stories, ideas, and half-perceived meanings.",
	"Neptune_Cancer": "With Neptune in Cancer, your spiritual ideals are deeply tied to home, family, and the past — a longing for belonging and rootedness that transcends the ordinary. Your imagination is nurtured by memory and emotional depth, and you may carry a poignant nostalgia for places and people that feel sacred to you.",
	"Neptune_Leo": "With Neptune in Leo, your ideals are dramatic, creative, and oriented toward the transcendence that comes through artistic expression and love. You may be drawn to glamour, performance, or idealized romance as vehicles for spiritual experience — seeking the divine in the radiance of creative self-expression.",
	"Neptune_Virgo": "With Neptune in Virgo, your spiritual ideals are grounded in service, healing, and practical compassion. You are drawn to the sacred in the everyday — in craft, in the body, in the desire to improve what is broken. The challenge is the tendency to sacrifice yourself in service to an ideal that can never be perfectly realized.",
	"Neptune_Libra": "With Neptune in Libra, your ideals are oriented toward perfect harmony, love, and beauty — a longing for an ideal partnership or world in which justice and aesthetic grace are one. Personally, this placement creates a deep sensitivity to beauty and a romantic idealism that can be both inspiring and vulnerable to disillusionment.",
	"Neptune_Scorpio": "With Neptune in Scorpio, your spiritual ideals are tied to psychological depth, transformation, and the dissolution of taboo. Personally, this placement creates an unusually complex inner life and a spiritual hunger that can only be satisfied at great depth — surface answers leave you cold.",
	"Neptune_Sagittarius": "With Neptune in Sagittarius, your ideals are philosophical, adventurous, and oriented toward universal meaning. You collectively questioned organized religion while pursuing spirituality in a more personal, expansive form. Personally, this placement creates a visionary inner life and a spiritual hunger for truth without borders.",
	"Neptune_Capricorn": "With Neptune in Capricorn, your generation is dissolving the traditional structures of authority and achievement, finding spiritual dimensions within the pragmatic world. Personally, this placement creates a subtle idealism about career and contribution — the boundaries between ambition and calling blur in instructive and sometimes confusing ways.",
	"Neptune_Aquarius": "With Neptune in Aquarius, your generation is dissolving the boundaries between the individual and the collective — a generation steeped in the fluid, hyperconnected realities of the digital age. Personally, this placement creates an idealism about community and human progress that is both inspiring and vulnerable to collective illusion.",
	"Neptune_Pisces": "With Neptune in Pisces, the planet is in its home sign — your generation carries a concentrated collective spiritual energy. The boundaries between imagination and reality, the personal and the universal, are unusually permeable. Personally, this placement generates extraordinary creative and spiritual sensitivity, with both the gifts of compassion and the real challenges of dissolution.",

	// ── PLUTO ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"Pluto_Aries": "With Pluto in Aries, the transformative force of individual will and pioneering energy shapes your generation's deepest power. Personally, this placement creates a compulsive drive toward self-reinvention and a willingness to tear down and rebuild your own identity from the ground up when necessary.",
	"Pluto_Taurus": "With Pluto in Taurus, the transformative force is applied to material reality — values, land, and the body. Personally, this placement creates a profound, sometimes compulsive relationship with physical security, resources, and the question of what is truly worth preserving.",
	"Pluto_Gemini": "With Pluto in Gemini, the transformative force runs through communication, information, and the mind. Personally, this placement creates an intense, probing intelligence — a mind that cannot rest until it has uncovered the hidden meaning beneath the surface of words and ideas.",
	"Pluto_Cancer": "With Pluto in Cancer, the transformative force runs through home, family, and national identity. Personally, this placement creates deep, sometimes obsessive attachments to roots, ancestry, and emotional security — and an equally powerful capacity for transformation when those roots are shaken.",
	"Pluto_Leo": "With Pluto in Leo, the transformative force is tied to ego, creative power, and individual identity. Personally, this placement creates a compulsive drive to create, express, and leave a powerful individual legacy. The shadow is pride and the need for control; the gift is an extraordinary creative and personal force.",
	"Pluto_Virgo": "With Pluto in Virgo, the transformative force runs through work, health, and systems of service. Personally, this placement creates an intense drive for self-improvement and a deep awareness of how bodies, environments, and systems can be healed or destroyed by what seems like small, everyday choices.",
	"Pluto_Libra": "With Pluto in Libra, the transformative force runs through relationships, justice, and partnership. Personally, this placement creates intense, transformative relationship experiences and a compulsive need for fairness — a refusal to accept inequality in intimate or social contexts.",
	"Pluto_Scorpio": "With Pluto in Scorpio, the planet is in its home sign — this is one of the most intensely transformative placements possible. Personally, this placement creates profound depth, psychological power, and an instinctive understanding of destruction and rebirth as a single continuous process. You are built for radical self-transformation.",
	"Pluto_Sagittarius": "With Pluto in Sagittarius, the transformative force runs through belief systems, philosophy, and the quest for truth. Personally, this placement creates an intense drive to dismantle false beliefs and rebuild your worldview from the ground up. Truth, for you, is not a comfort — it is a compulsion.",
	"Pluto_Capricorn": "With Pluto in Capricorn, the transformative force runs through power structures, institutions, and social authority. Personally, this placement creates a deep awareness of how systems of power operate — and an equally powerful drive to either dismantle or ascend those structures with clear-eyed, strategic intensity.",
	"Pluto_Aquarius": "With Pluto in Aquarius, the transformative force runs through collective humanity, technology, and revolutionary social change. Personally, this placement creates an intense drive toward collective transformation and a compulsive need to reimagine how human beings organize, connect, and govern themselves.",
	"Pluto_Pisces": "With Pluto in Pisces, the transformative force runs through spirituality, imagination, and the dissolution of boundaries between the self and the collective. Personally, this placement creates an unusually deep access to the unconscious — and a life shaped by the slow, profound transformation of your innermost spiritual foundations.",

	// ── ASC (RISING) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"ASC_Aries": "With Aries rising, you enter the world with directness, confidence, and a pioneering energy that others notice immediately. You come across as bold, independent, and slightly impatient — someone who prefers to lead rather than follow. Your physical presence is energetic and assertive, and you instinctively take the initiative in new situations.",
	"ASC_Taurus": "With Taurus rising, you project a calm, steady, and physically grounded presence. Others see you as reliable, patient, and aesthetically attuned — someone who radiates an earthy, unhurried confidence. You tend to move deliberately, speak slowly, and make others feel immediately at ease with your solid, reassuring manner.",
	"ASC_Gemini": "With Gemini rising, others first see you as quick, curious, and communicative — the person who seems to be thinking and talking simultaneously. Your physical manner is lively and animated, and you give the impression of someone who is always collecting impressions. You adapt easily and effortlessly to new people and environments.",
	"ASC_Cancer": "With Cancer rising, you project a soft, receptive, and emotionally attuned first impression. Others sense your empathy and protectiveness before they know much else about you. You may come across as somewhat shy or guarded at first, but once you feel safe your warm, nurturing nature becomes unmistakable.",
	"ASC_Leo": "With Leo rising, others notice you — your presence is warm, dramatic, and naturally commanding. There is a quality of radiance to how you carry yourself, and even when you are not performing you tend to be seen. You project confidence, generosity, and a certain regal ease that draws people toward you.",
	"ASC_Virgo": "With Virgo rising, you project a composed, perceptive, and subtly precise first impression. Others notice your intelligence and attentiveness — you seem to be observing and assessing even while appearing modest. Your manner is refined, efficient, and careful; you do not draw attention to yourself, but you miss very little.",
	"ASC_Libra": "With Libra rising, you are immediately perceived as charming, elegant, and diplomatic. Others feel comfortable around you because you have a natural gift for making people feel seen and appreciated. You instinctively smooth social situations and tend to present yourself with aesthetic care and a gracious manner.",
	"ASC_Scorpio": "With Scorpio rising, you project an intense, magnetic, and somewhat mysterious first impression. Others sense depth and power in you even before you speak — there is something penetrating about your gaze and something controlled about your manner that makes people curious about what lies beneath.",
	"ASC_Sagittarius": "With Sagittarius rising, you project enthusiasm, optimism, and a cheerful, adventurous energy that is immediately infectious. Others see you as open, direct, and larger than life — someone who is always moving toward the next horizon. Your manner is expansive and warm, and you tend to make others feel that life is full of possibility.",
	"ASC_Capricorn": "With Capricorn rising, you project a composed, serious, and quietly authoritative first impression. Others sense your competence and self-discipline before they know anything else about you. You may appear reserved at first meeting, but there is an underlying gravity to your presence that inspires confidence.",
	"ASC_Aquarius": "With Aquarius rising, others perceive you as unique, independent, and slightly unconventional — someone who clearly operates on their own terms. Your manner is friendly but somewhat detached, and there is a quality of cool originality to how you present yourself. You draw people who are interested in ideas and in individuals who think for themselves.",
	"ASC_Pisces": "With Pisces rising, you project a soft, dreamy, and empathic first impression. Others sense your sensitivity and imagination immediately — there is something fluid and otherworldly about your manner that is hard to pin down. You may appear gentle or elusive, but people tend to feel oddly understood in your presence.",

	// ── DSC (DESCENDANT) ─────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"DSC_Aries": "With your Descendant in Aries, you are drawn to partners who are bold, assertive, and independent — people who match or exceed your own energy and don't need much direction. You may project qualities of impulsiveness or combativeness onto others, or find yourself consistently attracted to those who push back against you. The lesson is developing your own directness within partnership rather than needing a partner to carry that energy for you.",
	"DSC_Taurus": "With your Descendant in Taurus, you are drawn to partners who are grounded, sensual, and emotionally stable — people who provide a steady, reliable presence. You may seek in a partner an earthy comfort and patience that complements your own nature. The lesson is learning to value persistence and physical groundedness in yourself as much as in the people you love.",
	"DSC_Gemini": "With your Descendant in Gemini, you are drawn to partners who are curious, communicative, and mentally stimulating. You are attracted to wit, versatility, and a quick intelligence that keeps you engaged. The lesson is developing your own communicative flexibility and embracing the full complexity of relationship rather than longing for something simpler.",
	"DSC_Cancer": "With your Descendant in Cancer, you are drawn to nurturing, emotionally sensitive partners who create a sense of home and belonging. You may project vulnerability or emotional neediness onto others rather than acknowledging those needs in yourself. The lesson is opening to emotional intimacy and allowing yourself to be cared for, not just the caregiver.",
	"DSC_Leo": "With your Descendant in Leo, you are drawn to partners who are warm, creative, and confident — people who bring a playful, generous vitality to the relationship. You may project pride or the need for recognition onto your partners. The lesson is allowing yourself to shine alongside a partner rather than only supporting their light.",
	"DSC_Virgo": "With your Descendant in Virgo, you are drawn to partners who are analytical, helpful, and attentive to detail. You are attracted to competence and a certain understated precision. The lesson is developing your own capacity for discernment and service — recognizing that the high standards you see in others reflect standards you hold, or could hold, for yourself.",
	"DSC_Libra": "With your Descendant in Libra, you are drawn to gracious, diplomatic, and aesthetically attuned partners who bring balance and refinement into your life. You seek harmony and fairness in your close relationships. The lesson is developing your own relational grace without losing yourself in the process of accommodating others.",
	"DSC_Scorpio": "With your Descendant in Scorpio, you are drawn to intense, psychologically complex, and powerfully magnetic partners. You may project your shadow side or your deepest desires onto others rather than owning them directly. The lesson is embracing your own depth and transformative power rather than seeking those qualities exclusively through relationship.",
	"DSC_Sagittarius": "With your Descendant in Sagittarius, you are drawn to adventurous, philosophical, and free-spirited partners who expand your world. You are attracted to people with a strong vision and a love of freedom. The lesson is developing your own adventurous spirit and philosophical independence — taking your own journey rather than living it vicariously through a partner.",
	"DSC_Capricorn": "With your Descendant in Capricorn, you are drawn to ambitious, reliable, and structured partners who bring discipline and long-term commitment to the relationship. You are attracted to competence and a certain gravitas. The lesson is developing your own inner authority and capacity for sustained effort without relying on a partner to embody those qualities.",
	"DSC_Aquarius": "With your Descendant in Aquarius, you are drawn to unconventional, intellectually independent, and freedom-loving partners who break you out of comfortable patterns. You are attracted to the unusual and the original. The lesson is developing your own radical individuality rather than depending on a partner to introduce that energy into your life.",
	"DSC_Pisces": "With your Descendant in Pisces, you are drawn to compassionate, creative, and spiritually attuned partners with a dreamy, empathic quality. You may project vulnerability, imagination, or spiritual longing onto partners rather than acknowledging those dimensions in yourself. The lesson is opening to compassion and the willingness to surrender to something larger than yourself.",

	// ── MC (MIDHEAVEN) ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"MC_Aries": "With your Midheaven in Aries, your public life and career are built on initiative, leadership, and the courage to be first. Your professional reputation is built on your boldness, directness, and willingness to take decisive action. Others see you at your most powerful when you are pioneering something new and uncharted.",
	"MC_Taurus": "With your Midheaven in Taurus, your career is built on patience, craftsmanship, and reliable value creation. Your public reputation is associated with beauty, quality, and a dependable earthy competence. Others know you as someone who builds things that last and who delivers on their promises, consistently and over time.",
	"MC_Gemini": "With your Midheaven in Gemini, your career is built on communication, versatility, and intellectual range. Your professional reputation is associated with wit, adaptability, and the ability to connect people and ideas across different worlds. You thrive in fields that reward language, information, and the capacity to work across multiple domains simultaneously.",
	"MC_Cancer": "With your Midheaven in Cancer, your career is built on nurturing, emotional intelligence, and the creation of a sense of belonging. Your public reputation is tied to your empathy and your ability to create environments where others feel genuinely cared for. You may be drawn to family-oriented work, caregiving, or roles that require deep emotional understanding.",
	"MC_Leo": "With your Midheaven in Leo, your career is built on creative leadership, self-expression, and the capacity to inspire. Your professional reputation shines brightest when you are in a role that allows you to perform, lead, or bring your unique vision to the world. You are remembered for your warmth, your confidence, and the distinctive stamp you put on everything you touch.",
	"MC_Virgo": "With your Midheaven in Virgo, your career is built on service, analytical precision, and the mastery of craft. Your public reputation is tied to your reliability, your attention to detail, and your willingness to do the necessary work without seeking the spotlight. Others trust your expertise because you are more interested in doing things right than looking impressive.",
	"MC_Libra": "With your Midheaven in Libra, your career is built on diplomacy, aesthetic vision, and the cultivation of fair, harmonious relationships. Your professional reputation is associated with grace, balance, and an ability to bring opposing parties together. You thrive professionally in environments that value beauty, justice, and collaborative intelligence.",
	"MC_Scorpio": "With your Midheaven in Scorpio, your career is built on depth, psychological insight, and the willingness to go where others will not. Your public reputation is tied to your intensity, your perceptiveness, and your capacity to transform whatever you touch. You thrive professionally in roles that involve investigation, power, or the management of significant resources and crises.",
	"MC_Sagittarius": "With your Midheaven in Sagittarius, your career is built on vision, exploration, and the communication of wisdom. Your professional reputation is associated with your philosophical perspective, your expansive energy, and your ability to inspire others toward a larger goal. You thrive in education, travel, publishing, philosophy, or any field that allows you to share your conviction.",
	"MC_Capricorn": "With your Midheaven in Capricorn, your career is built on ambition, structure, and the patient pursuit of authority. Your public reputation is tied to your discipline, your reliability, and the genuine respect you earn through sustained competence. You thrive professionally in hierarchical environments where your methodical approach and long-term vision can climb to the top.",
	"MC_Aquarius": "With your Midheaven in Aquarius, your career is built on innovation, humanitarian vision, and intellectual independence. Your public reputation is associated with your originality, your forward thinking, and your commitment to a more equitable or progressive future. You thrive professionally in fields that are disrupting established systems or advancing collective wellbeing.",
	"MC_Pisces": "With your Midheaven in Pisces, your career is built on compassion, imagination, and spiritual or artistic depth. Your public reputation is tied to your sensitivity, your creative gifts, and your ability to serve something larger than personal ambition. You thrive professionally in artistic, healing, or spiritually oriented fields where the invisible dimensions of life are taken seriously.",

	// ── IC (IMUM COELI) ──────────────────────────────────────────────────
	"IC_Aries": "With your IC in Aries, your psychological foundation was shaped by independence, conflict, or the need to forge your own identity very early in life. Your private self is energized by a kind of inner warrior — assertive, sometimes combative, and fiercely autonomous. Home, for you, is a place of action and self-determination more than quiet passivity.",
	"IC_Taurus": "With your IC in Taurus, your psychological foundation is grounded in sensory comfort, material stability, and a deep connection to the physical world. Your inner security is built on reliable physical environments — good food, beautiful surroundings, and financial predictability nourish you at the deepest level. At your core, you are more patient and earthy than you may outwardly appear.",
	"IC_Gemini": "With your IC in Gemini, your psychological foundation was shaped by communication, movement, and intellectual stimulation from an early age. Your private self is lively, adaptive, and word-filled — your inner world thinks constantly. Home, for you, is a place of conversation and ideas; you are most yourself in environments that keep your mind engaged.",
	"IC_Cancer": "With your IC in Cancer, your psychological foundation is deeply emotional and tied to family history and the powerful need for belonging. At your innermost core, you carry the imprint of your family and ancestors strongly. Emotional security and a true sense of home are foundational needs — without them, the rest of your life feels unsteady.",
	"IC_Leo": "With your IC in Leo, your psychological foundation was shaped by the need for creative self-expression and the experience of being seen as special. Your private self is proud, warm, and oriented toward creative play. Home, for you, needs to be a place where you can be fully yourself — a private space where the real you is celebrated without the need for performance.",
	"IC_Virgo": "With your IC in Virgo, your psychological foundation was shaped by service, precision, and a deep concern with doing things correctly. Your private self is analytical and somewhat self-critical; your standards for yourself in intimate settings are very high. Home functions best when it is organized, purposeful, and free from unnecessary disorder.",
	"IC_Libra": "With your IC in Libra, your psychological foundation was shaped by the need for harmony, beauty, and relational balance. Your inner world is oriented toward fairness and aesthetic comfort; privately, you are more relational and partnership-oriented than you may appear publicly. Home is most nurturing for you when it is a place of beauty, peace, and mutual consideration.",
	"IC_Scorpio": "With your IC in Scorpio, your psychological foundation was shaped by intensity, transformation, and the experience of emotional depth from an early age. Your private self is complex, psychologically attuned, and in possession of a deep inner power that others rarely see. Home carries the weight of what is unspoken — the hidden currents beneath the family surface.",
	"IC_Sagittarius": "With your IC in Sagittarius, your psychological foundation was shaped by philosophical exploration, cultural diversity, or a family background with an expansive, freedom-loving quality. Your private self is optimistic, curious, and oriented toward meaning. Home is most nourishing for you when it has an element of openness — space for ideas and the freedom to roam.",
	"IC_Capricorn": "With your IC in Capricorn, your psychological foundation was shaped by responsibility, structure, and the experience of having to be mature before your time. Your private self is serious, disciplined, and quietly ambitious — there is an elder energy at your psychological core. Home functions best when it reflects your hard-won sense of order and earned achievement.",
	"IC_Aquarius": "With your IC in Aquarius, your psychological foundation was shaped by unconventionality, independence, or a family background that broke from tradition in significant ways. Your private self is progressive, intellectually driven, and fundamentally individualistic — even in intimate settings, you need to be free to be different. Home is most nourishing when it honors your need for originality.",
	"IC_Pisces": "With your IC in Pisces, your psychological foundation was shaped by imagination, emotional fluidity, and possibly a sense of spiritual mystery at the heart of your early family life. Your private self is deeply compassionate, intuitive, and porous — you absorb the atmosphere of your home deeply. At your core, you are more sensitive and spiritually oriented than your public self may indicate.",
}
